templates.name: Fundamental Decomposition
templates.description: Break complex wholes into manageable parts. Works for problems, arguments, code, systems.

templates.name: Fundamental Synthesis
templates.description: Combine separate elements into unified wholes. Works for ideas, data, perspectives.

templates.name: Fundamental Comparison
templates.description: Analyze similarities and differences between items. Works for concepts, options, approaches.

templates.name: Fundamental Causal Reasoning
templates.description: Trace cause-effect relationships. Works for debugging, root cause analysis, predictions.

templates.name: Fundamental Analogy
templates.description: Apply patterns from familiar domains to new problems. Works for creative problem-solving.

templates.name: Fundamental Verification
templates.description: Check correctness of claims or solutions. Works for proofs, tests, validations.

templates.name: Fundamental Refinement
templates.description: Iteratively improve solutions. Works for optimization, editing, debugging.

templates.name: Fundamental Abstraction
templates.description: Extract general principles from specific cases. Works for learning, theory building.
